  "html": "<h1>Applies to</h1>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>PCI DSS Requirement 5.2</li>\r\n    <li>PCI DSS Requirement 5.2.b </li>\r\n    <li>PCI DSS Requirement 5.2.c</li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n  <h1>What to Do</h1>\r\n  <p>Configure the anti-virus to update itself and its definition files.</p>\r\n  <h1>Why</h1>\r\n  <p>The anti-virus definitions and anti-virus engine have to be updated frequently to be effective because malware threats evolve rapidly.\r\n</p>\r\n  <h1>How</h1>\r\n  <p>Verify that it is possible to run automatic updates with your anti-virus by referring to the vendor documentation or technical support. The documentation or technical support should provide the exact instructions on how to implement automatic updates. Automatic\r\n updates are a basic feature of modern anti-virus packages. If your anti-virus does not offer this feature, please consider installing and configuring a different anti-virus.</p>"
